    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `--clean`, `:syntax off` is inconsistently applied depending on the file type opened.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n`nvim --clean -O /tmp/wat.lua /tmp/wat.sh`\r\n\r\nWhen this starts up, highlighting is enabled. As expected. Now if you run `:syntax off`, the shell script un-highlights as expected, but the lua script does not.\r\n\r\nwhere:\r\n\r\n## `/tmp/wat.lua`:\r\n```         \r\nprint(\"But we have highlighting here.\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n## `/tmp/wat.sh`\r\n```\r\necho \"no highlighting here.\";\r\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -O /tmp/wat.lua /tmp/wat.sh\r\n:syntax off\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHighlighting should be disabled consistently.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS/24.05.20240520.baed31d\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 24.02.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix",
